
Placing an external monitor:

brew install displayplacer
displayplacer list  # Gives output that ends with something like:

displayplacer "id:XXXXXXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXXXXXXXXXX res:NNNNxNNNN
hz:NNN color_depth:N enabled:true scaling:on origin:(0,0) degree:0"
"id:XXXXXXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXXXXXXXXXX res:NNNNxNNNN hz:NN
color_depth:N enabled:true scaling:off origin:(N,N) degree:0"

"res" gives the logical resolution of each device and "origin"
specifies the device location (horizontal, vertical).  You can
tweak the output from displayplacer list and feed it back
as arguments to displayplacer to set a new orientation.
